\noindent
\textbf{Application for POWER BI Developer and MS Fabric}

\vspace{0.2cm}

% Main letter content
\justify
\setlength{\parindent}{0pt}
\setlength{\parskip}{12pt}

Dear Hiring Manager,

I am writing to express my interest in the Power BI Developer (MS Fabric) position in Berlin. With hands-on experience in Power BI development, MS Fabric, data modeling, ETL automation, and stakeholder engagement, I am confident in my ability to deliver impactful BI solutions aligned with your company’s data strategy.

In my BI roles at  Bosch and Siemens Healthineers, I designed and optimized end-to-end Power BI reporting solutions that supported operational and strategic decision-making across teams. I developed scalable semantic models, implemented efficient ETL workflows using Python, SQL, and Power Query, and introduced automation that significantly reduced manual reporting effort. I have consistently focused on performance tuning, KPI governance, and building intuitive dashboards that enhance data consumption for both technical and non-technical users.

What excites me most about this role is the strong focus on MS Fabric. I have worked with Fabric components including Lakehouse, Pipelines, Dataflows Gen2, and semantic models, building unified data layers that support enterprise BI. I also developed automated trigger-based workflows and integrated Python validation scripts to enhance reliability and maintain clean, analytics-ready datasets. My work emphasizes not only technical excellence but also business alignment—ensuring reporting solutions truly address stakeholder needs.

I thrive in agile environments, enjoy direct collaboration with business teams, and bring a proactive mindset to improving BI landscapes. I am also fully eligible to work in Germany and available to work onsite in Berlin as required.

I would welcome the opportunity to bring my experience in Power BI, MS Fabric, and data-driven problem solving to your team. Thank you for considering my application. I look forward to the possibility of discussing how I can contribute to your BI initiatives.

